The paper deals with the strategy synthesis problem for games with multi-dimensional mean-payoff and energy objectives along with a parity condition. This problem is related to the quantitative theory of verification and synthesis, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also involves the study of games with multiple objectives, which is a topic in Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of memory and randomness in strategies suggests a connection to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic approach to solving the problem, which is relevant to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
